- [ ] `IDisposable` resources are wrapped in `using` statements or blocks
- [ ] Async methods use `await` — no `.Result` or `.Wait()` (deadlock risk)
- [ ] Nullable reference types: no suppression operator (`!`) without justification
- [ ] No deserialization of untrusted data with `BinaryFormatter` (RCE vector)
- [ ] Exception handling catches specific types — no bare `catch (Exception)`
